<p itemprop="description">A lead data architect provides strategic leadership for data architecture across the organisation. They shape the organisation's data strategy, lead major transformation initiatives, and build high-performing data architecture teams.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define and execute organisation-wide data architecture vision and strategy</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead major data transformation programmes and strategic initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build and lead high-performing data architecture teams across multiple locations</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Influence senior leadership on data architecture investment decisions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish governance frameworks and architecture review processes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation in data architecture and emerging technologies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Represent the organisation in external data architecture forums and communities</li>
    </ul>
</section>

